{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-04-30T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Ships leaving Lisbon once passed a small stone tower before meeting the wide Atlantic. That tower, standing on the bank of the Tagus River, served as both a guardian and a farewell. Say hello to Belém Tower—a fortress that watched Portugal sail into the Age of Exploration.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_ROW0291299958_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BelemTowerBank_ROW0291299958_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Belém Tower on the bank of the Tagus River, Lisbon, Portugal","Copyright":"© f9photos/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Belem+Tower&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260429_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260429_BelemTowerBank"},"Ssd":"20260429","Name":"BelemTowerBank","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0291299958","FullDateString":"29 apr. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"The spectacled bear, also known as the Andean bear, is the only South American bear of the Ursidae family. Inhabiting the northern and central Andes Mountains, it dwells primarily in forested areas and feeds mainly on shoots and fruit. Pale markings around the eyes often resemble eyeglasses, or 'spectacles,' giving the species its distinctive name.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_ROW0128606931_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AndeanBear_ROW0128606931_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Spectacled bear resting in tree, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Spectacled+bear&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260428_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260428_AndeanBear"},"Ssd":"20260428","Name":"AndeanBear","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0128606931","FullDateString":"28 apr. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Designed by architect Giuseppe Mengoni and completed in 1877, the Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II in Milan, Italy, is one of the world's oldest and most famous shopping arcades. Located between Piazza del Duomo and Piazza della Scala, it features a stunning glass-and-iron roof and an elegant, octagonal layout. Affectionately known as 'Milan's living room,' the Galleria is home to high-end boutiques, historic cafés such as Caffè Biffi and Camparino in Galleria, and renowned restaurants.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_ROW9826130780_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MilanGalleria_ROW9826130780_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"The glass dome of Galleria Vittorio Emanuele II, Milan, Italy","Copyright":"© PhillipMinnis/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galleria+Vittorio+Emanuele+II+Milan+Italy&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260427_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260427_MilanGalleria"},"Ssd":"20260427","Name":"MilanGalleria","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9826130780","FullDateString":"27 apr. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring brings apple trees to life with clouds of soft pink blossoms. Their delicate petals brighten orchards and hillsides, standing out against clear blue skies as the season shifts from winter toward warmer days. These blooms attract pollinators such as bees and butterflies, helping fruit trees produce the apples that will grow later in the year.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_ROW9623403964_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.AppleBlossoms_ROW9623403964_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Pink apple blossoms, Avila Beach, California, United States","Copyright":"© Mimi Ditchie Photography/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Apple+tree&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260426_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260426_AppleBlossoms"},"Ssd":"20260426","Name":"AppleBlossoms","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9623403964","FullDateString":"26 apr. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Penguins usually bring Antarctica to mind, but these endearing flightless seabirds don't always follow the ice. Found only in the Galápagos Islands—a volcanic archipelago about 966 kilometres off Ecuador's coast—the Galápagos penguins pictured here live farther north than any other penguin. Cool, nutrient‑rich ocean currents make this equatorial habitat possible by supplying food and keeping surrounding waters within survivable temperatures. Compact and agile, these birds spend much of the day in the water to stay cool.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_ROW9365376155_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GalapagosPenguins_ROW9365376155_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Galápagos penguins swimming, Galápagos Islands, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Henley Spiers/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Galapagos+penguins&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260425_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260425_GalapagosPenguins"},"Ssd":"20260425","Name":"GalapagosPenguins","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9365376155","FullDateString":"25 apr. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"What happens when water moves too slowly to notice? In Everglades National Park, it shapes everything. Covering around 6,100 square kilometres, the park was established in 1947 to protect a wetland system unlike any other in the United States. As a recognised UNESCO World Heritage Site, the park's elevated pinelands rise above the marshes and prairies that form one of the world's largest wetland systems.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_ROW9169451135_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SlashPine_ROW9169451135_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Forest hammock of slash pine and saw palmetto, Everglades National Park, Florida, United States","Copyright":"© Mary Liz Austin/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Everglades+National+Park+Florida&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260424_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260424_SlashPine"},"Ssd":"20260424","Name":"SlashPine","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9169451135","FullDateString":"24 apr. 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Small, lively and instantly recognisable by its call: the chiffchaff is one of Germany's most common songbirds and a true harbinger of spring. As early as late February, the first males return from their winter quarters in the Mediterranean or south-western Europe and begin their distinctive song, which gives the species its name. This clear 'chiff-chaff, chiff-chaff' makes it easy to locate, even when it remains hidden in dense vegetation.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ChiffchaffSpring_ROW0928406195_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ChiffchaffSpring_ROW0928406195_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Common chiffchaff, Germany","Copyright":"© Andyworks/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260423_ChiffchaffSpring\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Common+chiffchaff&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260423_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260423_ChiffchaffSpring"},"Ssd":"20260423","Name":"ChiffchaffSpring","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0928406195","FullDateString":"23 apr. 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Located on the eastern Balkan Peninsula, Bulgaria sits at the crossroads of Europe and Asia, where ancient cultures, fertile landscapes and shifting climates converge.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_ROW5132279610_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BulgariaPlains_ROW5132279610_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Thunderstorm above the plains, Bulgaria","Copyright":"© Revolu7ion93/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Bulgaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260506_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260506_BulgariaPlains"},"Ssd":"20260506","Name":"BulgariaPlains","Market":"ROW","Hash":"5132279610","FullDateString":"6 maj 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"In the highlands of Jalisco, Mexico, rows of blue agave stretch across the landscape, their spiky leaves catching the light like a field of sculpted stars. This region, centred around the town of Tequila, is the birthplace of tequila, a spirit deeply tied to both land and tradition.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MayoAgave_ROW0279228757_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MayoAgave_ROW0279228757_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Field of blue agave near Tequila, Jalisco, Mexico","Copyright":"© Brian Overcast/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260505_MayoAgave\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Tequila+Jalisco+Mexico&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260505_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260505_MayoAgave"},"Ssd":"20260505","Name":"MayoAgave","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0279228757","FullDateString":"5 maj 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today's image takes us to Ksar Ouled Soltane in Tunisia's Tataouine district, where stacked clay granaries rise like sand-coloured fortresses. Dating back to the 15th century, this storehouse complex was built by Berber communities to protect harvests from heat, theft and time. Function first. Beauty as a side effect.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_ROW9968378030_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.KsarOuledSoltane_ROW9968378030_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Ksar Ouled Soltane, Tataouine district in southern Tunisia","Copyright":"© Dark_Eni/Getty Images Plus","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Ksar+Ouled+Soltane+Tataouine+district&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260504_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260504_KsarOuledSoltane"},"Ssd":"20260504","Name":"KsarOuledSoltane","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9968378030","FullDateString":"4 maj 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"High above the savannah in Kenya's Masai Mara National Reserve, a leopard curls up on a tree branch, napping as the grasslands glow at sunset. Today, let's throw light on one of the world's most adaptable big cats. Leopards roam across Africa and parts of Asia, thriving in habitats that range from forests and mountains to open savannas. Their spotted coats are unique to each individual, like fingerprints, and their powerful climbing skills allow them to stash prey high in trees, out of reach of scavengers.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_ROW2641665263_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.MasaiLeopard_ROW2641665263_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Leopard sleeping in a tree in the savannah, Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© Klein & Hubert/Nature Picture Library","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Masai+Mara+National+Reserve&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260503_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260503_MasaiLeopard"},"Ssd":"20260503","Name":"MasaiLeopard","Market":"ROW","Hash":"2641665263","FullDateString":"3 maj 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Can you picture 11,000 square kilometres of protected wilderness? That's Jasper National Park in Alberta. Established in 1907 as part of a growing network of protected landscapes in the Canadian Rockies, it was designated a national park in 1930. The park reflects both conservation efforts and much older Indigenous connections, including those of the Nakoda and Secwépemc peoples. Its terrain ranges from glacier-fed rivers and alpine meadows to dense conifer forests dominated by spruce and pine.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GreenJasper_ROW9272973075_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GreenJasper_ROW9272973075_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Small lake and marsh in Jasper National Park in Alberta, Canada","Copyright":"© Don White/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260502_GreenJasper\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Jasper+National+Park+Alberta&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260502_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260502_GreenJasper"},"Ssd":"20260502","Name":"GreenJasper","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9272973075","FullDateString":"2 maj 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"At the far edge of Ynys Llanddwyn, where the land quietly gives way to sea, Tŵr Mawr Lighthouse stands watch without making a fuss. It is not tall, not flashy, but it knows its purpose—and it keeps it bright.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_ROW9390350989_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.TwrMawrLighthouse2026_ROW9390350989_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Tŵr Mawr lighthouse on Llanddwyn Island in Anglesey, Wales","Copyright":"© Lukas Bischoff/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260501_TwrMawrLighthouse2026\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Twr+Mawr+Lighthouse&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260501_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260501_TwrMawrLighthouse2026"},"Ssd":"20260501","Name":"TwrMawrLighthouse2026","Market":"ROW","Hash":"9390350989","FullDateString":"1 maj 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Imagine a flower sparking a financial frenzy. Sounds unlikely, right? Yet in the 1630s, tulips did exactly that in the Netherlands. During tulip mania, rare bulbs became luxury items traded for astonishing sums—some valued at prices comparable to a house. Why so valuable? Unusual colours and striped patterns were scarce and unpredictable, and collectors wanted the rarest varieties they could find.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_ROW0532367282_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.DutchTulips_ROW0532367282_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Info","Title":"Grape hyacinths and tulips, Keukenhof Gardens, Lisse, Netherlands","Copyright":"© Martin Ruegner/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Keukenhof+Gardens&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260430_0700\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260430_DutchTulips"},"Ssd":"20260430","Name":"DutchTulips","Market":"ROW","Hash":"0532367282","FullDateString":"30 apr. 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Dagens bild","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Mer information","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donera nu","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Snabbfakta:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Nyligen använda startsidebilder","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Startsidebild {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"Denna dag i historien","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Den här dagen i {0} {1}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_SHARE_TOOLTIP":"Dela dagens Bing-s